│ Looking at the error and the code, I can see the issue more clearly now.    │
│ The problem is that when we're processing loops in a loop nest, we need to  │
│ ensure that we only mark loops as deleted that are either the current loop  │
│ being processed or subloops of it.                                          │
│                                                                             │
│ The assertion failure shows:                                                │
│ ```                                                                         │
│ assert((&L == CurrentL || CurrentL->contains(&L)) && "Cannot delete a loop  │
│ outside of the subloop tree currently being processed.")                    │
│ ```                                                                         │
